<br>
A few comments:<br>
<br>
1. BoBC aren't the best mage item. Shield of Auras, Halo of enlightened barriers, and the Spellshield wand from VT are arguably superior. The blazing sceptre of elements is a reasonable substitute for BoBC as well (less DPS, but 8 second casting time makes it easier to use)<br>
<br>
2. Most mobs won't low hp frenzy on you IF you wait for someone else to aggro them first AND you do absolutely nothing to bother the mob (like, say, using a pet on them). It's ok to mod down to a sliver of life during a pull as long as you wait for the cleric to CH you. Make sure your cleric is well trained though! Most unitiated clerics find a rodding magician wierd and bizzarre.<br>
<br>
3. You can mod down to negative 8 hit points safely, and negative 9 hit points if you are careful.<br>
<br>
4. Try to make rods before a major battle (and pick them up and drop them occasionally to refresh them). Most of the time there is no reason to amke a rod mid fight. All your mana can then go into nuking, and you can draw down from your own pile during the fight. This way, you really aren't even a support class on a big gfight... you are a pure nuking class.<br>
  <p>Master Cydmab Promethean, Fury's Edge <BR>
Arch Mage of Morell Thule
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugraccil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graccil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#333333>(6/11/02 11:11:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sonic.net/knightstribunal/misc/graccilsig.gif width=45 height=125 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Is that your best whine?</span><hr size=1> Very nice guide <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
When I drop rods, I look straight ahead in 3rd person view (with the camera directly above me) so that the people are smaller, and easilly out of range to trade.<br>
<br>
I also like to give rods out to everybody before a fight, it allows me greater freedom to nuke.<br>
<br>
Oh, and mod rods make you bleed, so modding down to negative anything = death unless you have some kind of regen spell up - tpp works.  I've gone unconcious before with rods, its fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table border="0" cellpadding="0"><td colspan='2'><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8972"><font size='2'>Master Graccil Baldinghead</font></a></b></td>
