<br>
Yes, any item with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rune</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or something like it rocks for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> even more than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  It can be used to prevent the damage dealt by rodding.<br>
<br>
However, another item slipped my mind as well.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velious Cleric Quest Greaves</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have a right-click effect, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Word of Health</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which is an AOE 100 point group heal.  The does not generate an unreasonable amount of aggro, being only 100 points.  However, three clicks of the pants, and that heals one click of the rod.  Most excellent.<br>
<br>
